    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON 16709 AND 16710 SERIES - REASSEMBLE - OUTPUT SHAFT AND REAR BEARING
        ASSEMBLIES (Figure 118)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="6">
        <title>OUTPUT SHAFT AND REAR BEARING ASSEMBLIES (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f13021b8">Figure 118</hotlnk>)
        </title>
        <figure id="f13021b8" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13021b8" filename="../figg13/G13021b8.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 118. Output Shaft &#38; Rear Bearing Assemblies</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">IMPORTANT: Mark two timing teeth on the synchronizer side of the LO Range gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021b9">Figure 119</hotlnk>). Teeth must be 180 degrees apart on the gear. Count the
                number of teeth between each tooth; they will be equal to each other.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021b9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021b9" filename="../figg13/G13021b9.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 119. Mark Timing Teeth</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the output shaft on a bench and install the spline washer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021c0">Figure 120</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021c0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021c0" filename="../figg13/G13021c0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 120. Install Spline Washer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the LO Range gear on the output shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021c1">left, Figure 121</hotlnk>). Before placing the washer on the shaft, apply some
                oil to the contact surfaces (right).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021c1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021c1" filename="../figg13/G13021c1.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 121. LO Range Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Heat the front bearing inner race and install it on the output shaft against the washer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021c2">Figure 122</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021c2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021c2" filename="../figg13/G13021c2.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 122. Front Bearing Inner Race</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Do not heat the bearing above 275&#176;F (136&#176;C).</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Compare the front bearing and rear bearing inner diameters. The front bearing inner diameter
                        is larger and installed first.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the auxiliary rear bearing race into the housing bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021c3">Figure 123</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021c3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021c3" filename="../figg13/G13021c3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 123. Auxiliary Bearing Race</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
